<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-09T11:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-09T11:44:00-05:00" n="432" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d432">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.7962/56: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-09T16:00:00-00:44">March 9,
                                    1942—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received March 9—3:41 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>63. From McBride. Legation’s 56, March 6, 11 p.m. Pending arrival of
                            nucleus force, it is believed urgent that some protection be provided
                            for Harbel Field immediately. Colonel Fox, Captain Beard, Wharton,
                            Firestone manager and I suggest that Captain Beard be authorized to
                            organize and instruct about 20 carefully selected Pan American
                            construction men now on field in use of 2 machine guns which Colonel
                            Kemp has made available from Accra. Weapons and ammunition to remain in
                            custody of two commissioned officers who are now here at all times. This
                            will not interfere with or delay Beard’s mission. [McBride.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>